kham, Lancashire, England":"Kirkham, Lancashire, England"},"nl":{"1104–":"1104–Overleden","1094–1170":"1094–1170","1123–Male":"1123–Overleden","1125–1185":"1125–1185","1129–Male":"1129–Overleden","1135–Male":"1135–Overleden","1158–Male":"1158–Overleden","1167–1216":"1167–1216","1104–Female":"1104–Overleden","1185":"1185","1094":"1094","1170":"1170","1129":"1129","1106":"1106","1216":"1216","1215":"1215","1104":"1104","1158":"1158","1125":"1125","1135":"1135","ABT 1167":"circa 1167","1167":"1167","1123":"1123","about 1125":"circa 1125","about 1158":"circa 1158","about 1123":"circa 1123","about 1135":"circa 1135","Singleton, Lancashire, England":"Singleton, Lancashire, England","Little Singleton, Kirkham, Lancashire, England":"Kirkham, Lancashire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","England":"England","Kirkham, Lancashire, England":"Kirkham, Lancashire, England"},"en":{"1104–":"1104–Deceased","1094–1170":"1094–1170","1123–Male":"1123–Deceased","1125–1185":"1125–1185","1129–Male":"1129–Deceased","1135–Male":"1135–Deceased","1158–Male":"1158–Deceased","1167–1216":"1167–1216","1104–Female":"1104–Deceased","1185":"1185","1094":"1094","1170":"1170","1129":"1129","1106":"1106","1216":"1216","1215":"1215","1104":"1104","1158":"1158","1125":"1125","1135":"1135","ABT 1167":"about 1167","1167":"1167","1123":"1123","about 1125":"about 1125","about 1158":"about 1158","about 1123":"about 1123","about 1135":"about 1135","Singleton, Lancashire, England":"Singleton, Lancashire, England","Little Singleton, Kirkham, Lancashire, England":"Kirkham, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom","England":"England","Kirkham, Lancashire, England":"Kirkham, Lancashire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Singleton","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Lancashire and West Yorkshire):","habitational name from Singleton (Lancashire), probably from Old English <i>scingol</i> ‘shingle, wooden roof tile’ + <i>tūn</i> ‘farmstead, estate’. Bearers of this surname are said to be descended from Ughtred <i>de Sinleton</i>, holder of lands in Amounderness wapentake (Lancashire) <i>c.</i> 1160–90. This name was first recorded in Ireland in 1308 and firmly established in Louth and Monaghan during the 17th century.","habitational name from Singleton (Sussex), probably from Old English <i>sængel</i>, <i>sengel</i> ‘bundle, tuft’ + <i>tūn</i> ‘farmstead, estate’."],"variants":[{"name":"Singelton","meanings":["English: variant of   Singleton  ."]},{"name":"Shingleton","meanings":["English: late medieval variant of   Singleton  ."]}]},{"name":"Hucca","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Angelo, Enrico, Marcello, Salvatore, Silvio.","Italian (Sicily):","in part a metonymic occupational name for a grower and seller of gourds (squashes or marrows), from Italian <i>zucca</i> ‘gourd’ (from Late Latin <i>cucutia</i>, from classical Latin <i>cucurbita</i>). More often, however, it is a nickname from the same word used in its colloquial transferred sense ‘head’, in particular ‘empty head’."],"variants":[{"name":"Zucconi","meanings":["Italian: patronymic or plural form of an augmentative of   Zucca   or of a nickname from <i>zuccone</i> ‘dull, stubborn’, also ‘bald’."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705185,"age":2,"year":"1106","julianDay":2125018,"title":"The Battle of Tichebray","description":"King Henry I defeated and captured his brother, Robert of Normandy, at the Battle of Tinchebray in 1106. Robert remained in captivity until his death in 1134.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705187,"age":111,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs Hucca de Singleton was born in 1104, in Singleton, Lancashire, England. She had at least 6 sons with Hucca de Singleton."},"et":{"1104–":"1104–Surnud","1094–1170":"1094–1170","1123–Male":"1123–Surnud","1125–1185":"1125–1185","1129–Male":"1129–Surnud","1135–Male":"1135–Surnud","1158–Male":"1158–Surnud","1167–1216":"1167–1216","1104–Female":"1104–Surnud","1185":"1185","1094":"1094","1170":"1170","1129":"1129","1106":"1106","1216":"1216","1215":"1215","1104":"1104","1158":"1158","1125":"1125","1135":"1135","ABT 1167":"umbes 1167","1167":"1167","1123":"1123","about 1125":"umbes 1125","about 1158":"umbes 1158","about 1123":"umbes 1123","about 1135":"umbes 1135","Singleton, Lancashire, England":"Singleton, Lancashire, England","Little Singleton, Kirkham, Lancashire, England":"Kirkham, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"England","Kirkham, Lancashire, England":"Kirkham, Lancashire, England"},"fi":{"1104–":"1104–Kuollut","1094–1170":"1094–1170","1123–Male":"1123–Kuollut","1125–1185":"1125–1185","1129–Male":"1129–Kuollut","1135–Male":"